definition: to come to prominence/to appear clearly/to stick out

sentences.english: The crown is decorated with a stunning black onyx cabochon.
sentences.chinese: 錶冠以一顆華麗的凸圓形黑縞瑪瑙裝飾。

sentences.chinese: 所述凸臺全部置於所述活塞頭右端的環狀槽內。

sentences.english: Our sky chart shows the bright waxing gibbous moon and the planet Jupiter for around mid-evening tonight.
sentences.chinese: 今日的星圖展示了午夜前後明亮的凸月和木星。

sentences.english: In this paper, we present two approaches to define convex fuzzy cone.

sentences.english: There are two kinds of reserviors consisting of clastics and carbonates in Yakela Black.

sentences.english: The wall juts out here to allow room for the chimney.
sentences.chinese: 牆在這裏凸了出來，以給煙囪留下位置。

sentences.english: Abnormal rearward curvature of the spine, resulting in protuberance of the upper back; hunchback.

sentences.english: Furthermore, posterior laminectomy will increase kyphotic deformity and instability.

sentences.english: Saugers have a fusiform body structure.

sentences.english: Some of the figures ornamented on the door came forward so that they looked real.

sentences.english: He is skinny, with hollow cheeks, humpbacked nose and thin lips.
sentences.chinese: 身材很瘦，高顴骨，凸鼻子，薄嘴脣。

sentences.english: Because of its raised deck, a well-placed hit underneath the vehicle could send it into a somersault.

sentences.english: Finally, carried out the stopped search procedure in the polyhedrons on the slices.

sentences.english: Constructing convex hull of planar point set is a basic algorithm in computational geometry.
